observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the MCPC prepare the following:

Council's Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the local development plan;

Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC);


Local Investment Plan for Children (LIPC);



Local State of Children's Report.

We recommended and the Management agreed to issue an Executive Order creating an Inventory Committee to conduct a comprehensive physical count of all PPE of the Municipality and submit the RPCPPE in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 and Section 124 of MNGAS for LGUs Volume 1.

We also recommended and the Municipal Accountant and the GSO agreed to prepare, using the prescribed format, the respective PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards; and perform a reconciliation of the reported PPEs per physical count, accounting, and property records to establish the correct balance of the PPE accounts in the financial statements.

Lastly, we recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to the following:
Ensure proper computation and reporting of the related depreciation expense;
Provide for residual values of PPEs, when applicable;
Record in the appropriate PPE accounts those capitalizable transactions charged in the Trust Fund in CY 2024;
Comply with the derecognition requirement for tangible items that fall below the capitalization threshold of ₱50,000.00, which are still part of the PPE costs pursuant to COA Circular No. 2022-004; and
Make the necessary journal entries to effect the required adjustments, to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the reported PPE balances, and achieve fair presentation of the financial statements.

We recommended and the concerned officials agreed to specify the period covered by the cash advance in the DV, and adhere to the limitation of three (3) months requirement, per Item 6.1.5 of COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01;

We also recommended and the certifying officials agreed to indicate the date of signing the DV and releasing of check to the payee to properly identify the reckoning date of its submission to the Office of the Auditor;

We likewise recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to submit the lacking documents to the Office of the Auditor, pursuant to Items 6.1.7 and 6.1.8 of COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01; and

We further recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to submit to the Office of the Auditor, the cash advance vouchers for the confidential fund, its transmittal letter and supporting documents in a sealed envelope within 7 days from the release of the check, in accordance with Item 6.1.8.4 of COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01.

We recommended and the MENRO and concerned personnel agreed to:

a)	Provide assistance to the barangays in the management of their solid waste and actively promote and enforce the sorting and segregation of wastes at the household level and all other sources;

b)	Ensure that collection of biodegradable/compostable and reusable/recyclable wastes is being done at the barangay level and only non-recyclable materials and special wastes shall be collected pursuant to pertinent provisions of Section 10 of RA No. 9003;

c)	Establish a policy for the generation of revenue from saleable recyclables and include the same in the Municipal Revenue Code; and



d)	Prepare a comprehensive work and financial plan relative to solid waste management operations to establish the timing and extent of implementation of each program, project and activities during the year and to employ monitoring mechanisms to ensure full implementation thereof.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the concerned officials and employees to take immediate actions on the matters listed below:

Set-up and maintain a GAD Database that will serve as basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation;

Ensure the full utilization of the allocated budget and propose plans/ programs for GAD, PWDs and the Youth to maximize the funds and benefits thereof and ensure that the relevant LGU PPAs and GAD activities will address/respond to the gender issues identified.

We recommended that the MCPC prepare the following:

Council's Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the local development plan;
Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC);
Local Investment Plan for Children (LIPC);
Local State of Children's Report.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to direct the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Treasurer and other personnel responsible to strictly adhere with the aforementioned provisions by submitting the following documents: 

Daily Time Record;
Document to support that the officials/personnel/workers were authorized to physically report for work at their assigned work stations on the prescribed official working hours by the head of agency/office during the implementation of state of national emergency in the area of such office or work station; 
Certification from the HR that the JOs were assigned in hospital, laboratories, or medical and quarantine facilities; and
List of official duties and responsibilities of the frontline HRHs.

