Recommendations:
We recommended that:
the LCE directly instruct the concerned employees to ensure that components of the Municipal Solid Waste Management (SWM) will be encompassed entirely and implemented in adherence to RA No. 9003;
the SWM Board ensure that the collections for specific types of wastes shall cover all the barangays in the Municipality;
the Municipality require the strict implementation of waste segregation at source through coordination with the Barangay Officials on the campaign of proper segregation and disposal of such wastes; and
the Officer-in-Charge on the collection of wastes be equipped with proper personal protective gear and observe the use of separate compartment/container with cover for specific types of wastes to ensure the containment of solid wastes while in transit.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the LCE and MCPC:
Adhere strictly to the provisions of DILG Memorandum Circular 2012-120 in the allocation and utilization of the 1% IRA for the strengthening and implementation of programs, projects and activities of the Local Council for the Protection of Children;
Update the MCPC to include only personnel currently connected with the Municipality and conduct meetings to discuss the program implementation strategies, issues and problems on children and monitoring of children’s PPAs in the locality; and
The MCPC to prepare the following:
Council's Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the local development plan;
Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC);
Local Investment Plan for Children (LIPC);
Local State of Children's Report.

We also recommended the following: 

Implement separate collection schedules for specific types of wastes, and ensure that such shall cover majority if not all of the barangays in the Municipality;
Observe the use of separate compartment/container with cover for specific types of wastes  and ensure the containment of solid wastes while in transit; 
Coordinate with Barangay Officials regarding information dissemination/ campaign on proper segregation and disposal of wastes to be implemented in the barangay;
Impose strictly MO No. 2004-21 to ensure source of fund for the full implementation of the SWM Program.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the LCE direct the concerned officials and employees in-charge/assigned in the implementation of the SWM Program in the Municipality to adhere strictly to the provisions of RA No. 9003.
